  "prompt": "Why there are so many private schools in India?",
  "response": "There are several reasons for the proliferation of private schools in India:\n\n1. Quality of Education\n- Perceived higher quality compared to government schools\n- Better infrastructure and facilities\n- More qualified and motivated teachers\n- English medium instruction\n\n2. Educational Demand\n- Growing middle-class population\n- Increasing aspiration for quality education\n- Limited seats in government schools\n- Population growth\n\n3. Government Policy\n- Liberalization of education sector\n- Reduced bureaucratic restrictions\n- Easier process for establishing schools\n- Public-private partnership models\n\n4. Economic Factors\n- Low government investment in public education\n- Relative affordability of private schools\n- Entrepreneurial opportunities in education sector\n\n5. Societal Preferences\n- Perception of social status\n- Better career opportunities for students\n- Emphasis on English language skills\n- Academic performance and competition\n\n6. Weak Public Education System\n- Inadequate government school infrastructure\n- Teacher absenteeism\n- Poor learning outcomes\n- Lack of modern teaching methodologies\n\n7. Demographic Dividend\n- Large young population\n- Growing demand for quality education\n- Parental investment in children's future\n\nThese factors collectively contribute to the significant presence of private schools across India.",
